      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Ran, and took a sponge.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " According to St. John, Jesus had just said, \"I thirst.\" The sponge and the wine were provided for the purpose of ministering some relief to the crucified. Common humanity was not quite extinct even in the executioners and spectators. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Vinegar",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The acid wine used by the soldiers, and called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "posca",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (see on ver. 34). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Put it on a reed.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " St. John calls it a stalk of hyssop; and if this is the caller plant, it, though of a climbing nature, can produce a stick some three or four feet long (see on ver. 29). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Gave him to drink",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐπότιζεν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", imperf., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "was offering him to drink",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); perhaps with the idea of helping him to endure till Elijah came. Thus was fulfilled the psalmist's word, \"In my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 69:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Matthew 27:48",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Vinegar (ὄξους)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Sour wine; the posca or ordinary drink of the Roman soldiers.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Gave him to drink (ἐπότιζεν)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The imperfect tense implies was in the act of giving, or about to give. At this point the Jews standing near interposed, saying, Let be (ἄφες)! \"Stop! Do not give him the drink. Let us see if Elijah will come to his aid.\" ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]